## A Single Degree [/degrees/{id}]

### List a degree with the given {id} [GET]
Gives back information for a single degree plus a list of universities that offer that degree.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
                "id": 0,
                "name": "Engineering",
                "num_public_offer": 5,
                "num_private_offer": 50,
                "num_percent_public": 6.75,
                "num_percent_private": 7.98,
                "universities": [ 
                {"university_id":0, "university_name":"The University of Texas at Austin"},
                {"university_id":0, "university_name":"St. Edward's"}
                ]
            }
            
## Search [/search]

### Search based on given query parameters [GET]
Give ordered search results based on given query parameters.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {"name": "Texas", "type": "states", "id": 1, "matching_words": ["Texas"], "match_type": "and"},
            {"name": "Texas State University", "type": "universities", "id": 34, "matching_words": ["Texas"], "match_type": "and"}
        ]